edu.cmu.cs.lti.discoursedb.core.repository

Interface CustomPagingAndSortingRepository<T,ID extends Serializable>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CustomCrudRepository<T,ID>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<T,ID>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AnnotationAggregateRepository, AnnotationInstanceRepository, AudienceRepository, BaseRepository<T,ID>, ContentRepository, ContributionAudienceRepository, ContributionContextRepository, ContributionInteractionRepository, ContributionRepository, DataSourceAggregateRepository, DataSourceInstanceRepository, DiscourseDBRepository, DiscoursePartContributionRepository, DiscoursePartInteractionRepository, DiscoursePartRelationRepository, DiscoursePartRepository, DiscourseRelationRepository, DiscourseRepository, DiscourseToDiscoursePartRepository, FeatureRepository, GroupRepository, UserRelationRepository, UserRepository

    @NoRepositoryBean
public interface CustomPagingAndSortingRepository<T,ID extends Serializable>
extends CustomCrudRepository<T,ID>
    This is a fork of the Spring Data PagingAndSortingRepository that makes use of DiscourseDB-specific customizations, such as consistently returning Optionals.
